article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 55, Savannah St. 29
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. -- C.J. Reed scored 14 points to lead Bethune-Cookman to a 55-29 victory over Savannah State on Tuesday night. Alvin Pegues added 12 points for the Wildcats (6-6), who led 30-12 at halftime. Savannah State (7-6) shot just 26.7 percent in the first half (4 of 15) and 26.5 for the game (9 of 34). The Tigers also committed 21 turnovers and shot only 43.8 percent from the free-throw line (7 of 16). Jovonni Shuler led Savannah State with 12 points and Chris Linton had 10 rebounds. Alexander Starling had 11 rebounds for Bethune-Cookman.
